{
  "texts": [
    "OASST1 pairwise rlhf reward foot_40 is a representative dataset in this category.",
    "It undergoes post-processing on the OASST1 (Wang et al, 2023a), generating data directly used for RLHF.",
    "The dialogues in the OASST1, constructed by humans and accompanied by quality ratings, allow for direct sorting of different responses based on annotations, reflecting human preferences.",
    "The scoring method involves assigning scores within a certain range to several responses to the same question.",
    "This method provides a continuous evaluation, offering a more flexible representation of preference intensity, allowing the model to understand human preferences in a more nuanced manner."
  ]
}